WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.389 --> 00:00:13.869
- [person] Hello. there.
- Hey. there.

2
00:00:14.307 --> 00:00:15.433
- Hi. Ted.
- Howdy.

3
00:00:16.017 --> 00:00:17.851
Hey. Ted. Good luck this weekend.

4
00:00:17.852 --> 00:00:19.311
I appreciate you. Susan. [chuckles]

5
00:00:19.312 --> 00:00:21.648
[imitates barking. chuckles]

6
00:00:22.148 --> 00:00:24.484
Hey. Ms. Barnaby. Rough night?

7
00:00:25.068 --> 00:00:28.070
Ted. if it's not rough. it isn't fun.

8
00:00:28.071 --> 00:00:29.573
[growls. chuckles]

9
00:00:30.240 --> 00:00:31.491
Ooh. boy.

10
00:00:32.284 --> 00:00:34.202
- Hiya.
- Hey. fellas. How you doing?

11
00:00:35.287 --> 00:00:37.121
- [person 2] What's up. Coach?
- There she is.

12
00:00:37.122 --> 00:00:41.375
Hey. wanker. Don't get all cocky
and fuck up that streak you're on.

13
00:00:41.376 --> 00:00:43.002
What streak?

14
00:00:43.003 --> 00:00:45.672
- Go Richmond.
- Yes. sir. [chuckles]

15
00:00:47.090 --> 00:00:48.133
Morning.

16
00:00:49.009 --> 00:00:50.010
Hey. How you doing?

17
00:00:55.390 --> 00:00:57.142
- Mom?
- Hey. Teddy.

18
00:00:59.227 --> 00:01:01.479
{\an8}[theme song plays]

19
00:01:29.883 --> 00:01:31.759
Don't think the cleaners
actually cleaned the floor.

20
00:01:31.760 --> 00:01:33.302
There are no cleaners.

21
00:01:33.303 --> 00:01:35.095
So. why do we put the chairs
on the tables?

22
00:01:35.096 --> 00:01:36.805
The patriarchy.

23
00:01:36.806 --> 00:01:40.518
{\an8}Oh. okay. Oh. well. I'll just. um...
Just go get a broom.

24
00:01:42.187 --> 00:01:44.021
{\an8}[door opens. closes]

25
00:01:44.022 --> 00:01:45.899
[whispers indistinctly]

26
00:01:46.483 --> 00:01:47.483
{\an8}Hello.

27
00:01:47.484 --> 00:01:50.819
{\an8}We're not open for another half hour.
Would you care to wait not here?

28
00:01:50.820 --> 00:01:51.904
{\an8}- I'm sorry.
- Okay.

29
00:01:51.905 --> 00:01:53.530
{\an8}- No. wait.
- [sighs]

30
00:01:53.531 --> 00:01:56.618
{\an8}We're actually here to speak
with Nathan Shelley. He works here. yeah?

31
00:01:57.369 --> 00:01:58.369
No such man exists.

32
00:01:58.370 --> 00:02:01.456
[Nathan whistles. hums]

33
00:02:02.415 --> 00:02:03.833
Oh. my God. it's true.

34
00:02:04.542 --> 00:02:07.087
[stammers]
How did you go through your money so fast?

35
00:02:08.087 --> 00:02:09.672
Did you get addicted to the limelight?

36
00:02:09.673 --> 00:02:13.051
What? No.
No. I just... I just like working here.

37
00:02:14.594 --> 00:02:16.194
I like spending time with my girlfriend.

38
00:02:17.597 --> 00:02:18.847
She was right there.

39
00:02:18.848 --> 00:02:22.477
- That... That was my girlfriend. She...
- Mm-hmm. Okay.

40
00:02:23.478 --> 00:02:24.603
What are you guys doing here?

41
00:02:24.604 --> 00:02:26.356
We want you to come back to Richmond.

42
00:02:30.110 --> 00:02:32.653
- You do?
- Yeah. bruv.

43
00:02:32.654 --> 00:02:35.156
'Cause this shit here is sad as fuck.

44
00:02:36.408 --> 00:02:38.952
{\an8}And a-all of you? You want me to come...

45
00:02:39.536 --> 00:02:41.746
{\an8}Yeah. It'll be good to have you back.

46
00:02:43.456 --> 00:02:45.749
{\an8}The whole team talked about it.
and it was unanimous.

47
00:02:45.750 --> 00:02:46.835
{\an8}Except for Bumbercatch.

48
00:02:47.836 --> 00:02:50.337
Who abstained
because he's passionately antidemocratic.

49
00:02:50.338 --> 00:02:51.964
Oh. yeah. [chuckles]

50
00:02:51.965 --> 00:02:53.049
Yeah.

51
00:02:53.633 --> 00:02:56.510
{\an8}So. what? Ted asked you guys
to come here to get me to come back?

52
00:02:56.511 --> 00:02:58.305
Uh. no. Ted doesn't know about it.

53
00:02:59.890 --> 00:03:02.016
{\an8}Yeah. no. we wanted to ask you
to see if you wanted to come back

54
00:03:02.017 --> 00:03:03.559
{\an8}before we approached Ted.

55
00:03:03.560 --> 00:03:04.977
{\an8}Okay. well. sorry. guys.

56
00:03:04.978 --> 00:03:07.771
{\an8}I don't think it's a good idea
for me to come back to Richmond. so...

57
00:03:07.772 --> 00:03:08.773
{\an8}Thank you though.

58
00:03:10.150 --> 00:03:11.050
Oh.

59
00:03:12.569 --> 00:03:13.570
{\an8}- Okay.
- Cool.

60
00:03:14.154 --> 00:03:15.822
{\an8}Can I have 75 kebabs to go?

61
00:03:16.406 --> 00:03:19.491
{\an8}Uh. yeah. Oh. yeah. No. of course.
Um. chicken. pork or lamb?

62
00:03:19.492 --> 00:03:20.577
Ooh.

63
00:03:21.995 --> 00:03:23.871
Or 25 of each? [stammers]

64
00:03:23.872 --> 00:03:26.332
- [chuckles] Nate the Great.
- [fingers snap]

65
00:03:26.333 --> 00:03:28.876
- [Colin chuckles] Yum.
- Okay.

66
00:03:28.877 --> 00:03:30.294
- Nice.
- Hey.

67
00:03:30.295 --> 00:03:32.172
- [Nathan humming]
- Thank you!

68
00:03:43.016 --> 00:03:44.476
[Mom] Pretty sparse.

69
00:03:45.685 --> 00:03:47.895
- [phone chimes]
- [exhales heavily]

70
00:03:47.896 --> 00:03:50.440
{\an8}Ooh. Mmm.

71
00:03:52.901 --> 00:03:55.277
{\an8}What are all these
crazy symbols on your oven dial?

72
00:03:55.278 --> 00:03:59.615
{\an8}[chuckles] Yeah. um. well. the one with
the line under the nuclear power symbol.

73
00:03:59.616 --> 00:04:01.033
{\an8}that's for making cookies and chicken.

74
00:04:01.034 --> 00:04:04.119
{\an8}The. uh. three squiggly lines
let you burn a frozen pizza.

75
00:04:04.120 --> 00:04:06.372
{\an8}And the key symbol there.
that makes the whole thing beep

76
00:04:06.373 --> 00:04:08.290
{\an8}until Beard comes over
and fixes it for me.

77
00:04:08.291 --> 00:04:09.541
{\an8}Is everything okay. Mom?

78
00:04:09.542 --> 00:04:11.335
{\an8}Oh. sure. I'm just looking around.

79
00:04:11.336 --> 00:04:14.505
{\an8}No. no. No. I mean. you being here
in London. Is everything okay?

80
00:04:14.506 --> 00:04:16.549
- Oh. yeah. Everything's fine.
- Uh-huh.

81
00:04:16.550 --> 00:04:18.092
I just always wanted to see England.

82
00:04:18.093 --> 00:04:20.762
so I booked this trip
as a little Mother's Day gift to myself.

83
00:04:21.346 --> 00:04:24.223
{\an8}Hmm. Okay. Well. um.
I mean. how long you been here?

84
00:04:24.224 --> 00:04:26.850
- Just a week.
- A week? Where the heck you staying?

85
00:04:26.851 --> 00:04:28.602
This adorable little hostel.

86
00:04:28.603 --> 00:04:30.813
{\an8}- Mom...
- Now. I met so many Australians.

87
00:04:30.814 --> 00:04:32.648
{\an8}They are backpacking through Europe.

88
00:04:32.649 --> 00:04:34.692
- Uh-huh.
- So much sex.

89
00:04:34.693 --> 00:04:36.443
- Mom.
- No. not me.

90
00:04:36.444 --> 00:04:38.195
- The Australians.
- No. no. I get it. Okay.

91
00:04:38.196 --> 00:04:40.864
Uh. well. look. how about you stay here
for the rest of your trip. all right?

92
00:04:40.865 --> 00:04:42.408
Only if I'm not a hassle.

93
00:04:42.409 --> 00:04:44.577
You're not a hassle. Mom. okay?
Please stay here.

94
00:04:44.578 --> 00:04:46.203
- Okay.
- Okay. good. All right.

95
00:04:46.204 --> 00:04:49.081
- Now. look. I gotta get to work.
- All righty. Have fun.

96
00:04:49.082 --> 00:04:52.459
{\an8}Um. You wanna tag along?

97
00:04:52.460 --> 00:04:55.796
- Well. I don't wanna be in your hair.
- Mom. I want you in my hair. Okay?

98
00:04:55.797 --> 00:04:58.257
I want you in my friends'
and coworkers' hair.

99
00:04:58.258 --> 00:04:59.800
Now. please. Come on with.

100
00:04:59.801 --> 00:05:01.552
- Okay. thank you. I would like that.
- All right. good.

101
00:05:01.553 --> 00:05:03.345
{\an8}You don't have to bring
your suitcase. Mom.

102
00:05:03.346 --> 00:05:06.098
{\an8}- Okay. I'll just grab my coat...
- Yeah.

103
00:05:06.099 --> 00:05:10.269
...get my bag... [singsongs]
...leave my worries on the doorstep.

104
00:05:10.270 --> 00:05:13.899
{\an8}Yeah. just direct your feet that way.
Mom. Okay. [groans]

105
00:05:18.862 --> 00:05:22.364
{\an8}Uh. Sam. Richmond have won
15 matches in a row.

106
00:05:22.365 --> 00:05:24.241
{\an8}With two games left.
you're just four points off

107
00:05:24.242 --> 00:05:26.494
{\an8}Manchester City
for the Premier League title.

108
00:05:27.245 --> 00:05:30.915
- Do you have a question?
- Yeah. Am I dreaming?

109
00:05:30.916 --> 00:05:32.125
[laughing]

110
00:05:32.792 --> 00:05:35.586
Uh. well. if you are. please.
don't wake up.

111
00:05:35.587 --> 00:05:37.630
And if this is the Matrix.
don't unplug me.

112
00:05:37.631 --> 00:05:39.173
[laughing]

113
00:05:39.174 --> 00:05:41.342
{\an8}Uh. Yeah. better Trent.

114
00:05:41.343 --> 00:05:43.928
{\an8}Uh. Marcus Adebayo. <i>The Independent</i>.

115
00:05:43.929 --> 00:05:47.139
{\an8}Uh. Jamie. on the heels of making
your England debut.

116
00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:49.660
how does it feel to be named
Premier League Player of the Month?

117
00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:56.440
{\an8}Uh. Um. yeah.
Uh. yeah. It feels good. I guess.

118
00:05:56.441 --> 00:05:59.443
{\an8}But it's. um... it's really the-the team
making me look good.

119
00:05:59.444 --> 00:06:02.697
{\an8}So. I should be doing a better job
of making them look good. really.

120
00:06:04.032 --> 00:06:06.034
So. yeah. Makes me... Makes me feel bad.

121
00:06:06.618 --> 00:06:08.286
[murmuring]

122
00:06:09.120 --> 00:06:11.705
Uh. Jamie also led the league
in assists this month.

123
00:06:11.706 --> 00:06:14.458
so he's done plenty to make
his teammates look good.

124
00:06:14.459 --> 00:06:16.293
Yeah. but they're the ones
who took all the shots.

125
00:06:16.294 --> 00:06:17.795
{\an8}Uh. he also scored a goal.

126
00:06:17.796 --> 00:06:20.298
{\an8}Uh. that was meant to be a pass.
You shouldn't count that.

127
00:06:21.800 --> 00:06:24.928
{\an8}That goal is a lie.
It should be retracted from the records.

128
00:06:26.096 --> 00:06:28.682
I apolog... I apologize to everyone.
especially the kids.

129
00:06:29.391 --> 00:06:31.058
[murmuring continues]

130
00:06:31.059 --> 00:06:34.062
{\an8}Right. let's call it there. everyone.
That was great. Thanks very much.

131
00:06:38.024 --> 00:06:39.692
- Hey. Boss.
- Oh. hello. Ted.

132
00:06:39.693 --> 00:06:42.861
Uh. so this morning.
I don't just bring biscuits.

133
00:06:42.862 --> 00:06:45.489
I also have a very special surprise guest.

134
00:06:45.490 --> 00:06:48.492
Oh. How exciting.
To whom do I owe the pleasure?

135
00:06:48.493 --> 00:06:50.327
I'm Coach Lasso's new bodyguard.

136
00:06:50.328 --> 00:06:51.954
Please keep your hands
where I can see them.

137
00:06:51.955 --> 00:06:55.124
- [Ted sighs]
- [chuckles] I'm just kidding.

138
00:06:55.125 --> 00:06:57.835
You can keep them well-manicured
mitts of yours wherever you like.

139
00:06:57.836 --> 00:07:00.462
- [Ted sighs]
- Oh. my God. You're Ted's mother.

140
00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:02.006
Winner. winner. B. F. Skinner.

141
00:07:02.007 --> 00:07:03.382
[chuckles]

142
00:07:03.383 --> 00:07:06.844
Mom. this is my boss. Rebecca Welton.
Rebecca. this is Dottie Lasso.

143
00:07:06.845 --> 00:07:08.429
- [gasps]
- Oh. honey. bring that in.

144
00:07:08.430 --> 00:07:10.264
- Oh. [laughs]
- [laughs]

145
00:07:10.265 --> 00:07:13.475
I can't believe I'm finally getting
to meet the woman who created

146
00:07:13.476 --> 00:07:15.311
one of the nicest humans I've ever met.

147
00:07:15.312 --> 00:07:16.770
Oh. no. don't look at me.

148
00:07:16.771 --> 00:07:19.565
This one popped out and immediately
asked the doctor if he needed anything.

149
00:07:19.566 --> 00:07:20.649
Oh. [chuckles]

150
00:07:20.650 --> 00:07:22.276
[chuckles] That doesn't make any sense.

151
00:07:22.277 --> 00:07:24.987
Babies can't talk and nor do they
understand empathy. And you know...

152
00:07:24.988 --> 00:07:27.448
[stammers] Dottie... I'm sorry.
May I call you Dottie?

153
00:07:27.449 --> 00:07:28.991
Sure. if you want me to respond.

154
00:07:28.992 --> 00:07:31.535
Right. If you'd like.
I'd love to show you around.

155
00:07:31.536 --> 00:07:34.039
Oh. I've heard great things
about the Sherlock Holmes Museum.

156
00:07:34.789 --> 00:07:35.915
I mean around the facility.

157
00:07:35.916 --> 00:07:38.584
Even better.
I can't wait to meet Dani Rojas.

158
00:07:38.585 --> 00:07:40.461
Oh. and he does not disappoint.

159
00:07:40.462 --> 00:07:42.254
- Oh. [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Shall we?

160
00:07:42.255 --> 00:07:43.964
Sure. [chuckles]

161
00:07:43.965 --> 00:07:45.675
- Where you from. honey?
- Surrey.

162
00:07:46.301 --> 00:07:47.510
Where are you from?

163
00:07:48.094 --> 00:07:50.596
- Surrey.
- Oh. I thought you said "sorry."

164
00:07:50.597 --> 00:07:51.681
[Rebecca chuckles]

165
00:07:53.600 --> 00:07:54.600
[groans]

166
00:07:54.601 --> 00:07:56.685
[laughing]

167
00:07:56.686 --> 00:07:57.770
So I say.

168
00:07:57.771 --> 00:07:59.730
"Officer. you must be mistaken.

169
00:07:59.731 --> 00:08:03.442
You couldn't have arrested my son.
My son is asleep in his own bed."

170
00:08:03.443 --> 00:08:04.526
[laughing]

171
00:08:04.527 --> 00:08:07.238
Are you sure you do not want
a kebab. Mama Lasso?

172
00:08:07.239 --> 00:08:08.614
Oh. no. thank you. Dani.

173
00:08:08.615 --> 00:08:10.282
You are so polite.

174
00:08:10.283 --> 00:08:12.993
- [team laughing]
- [Dottie] Okay. now bear with me.

175
00:08:12.994 --> 00:08:14.204
Mmm.

176
00:08:14.871 --> 00:08:17.289
It must be so lovely
having your mother visiting. Ted.

177
00:08:17.290 --> 00:08:18.750
Oh. yeah. It's great.

178
00:08:19.376 --> 00:08:21.460
- Oklahoma.
- Oh. no. It's weird.

179
00:08:21.461 --> 00:08:23.128
Mm-mmm.
Didn't even tell me she was coming.

180
00:08:23.129 --> 00:08:25.089
Just showed up out of nowhere.
you know. like one of them

181
00:08:25.090 --> 00:08:27.967
weird eyebrow hairs I started getting
the day after I turned 40.

182
00:08:27.968 --> 00:08:30.469
Mmm. That's what mothers do. Ted.

183
00:08:30.470 --> 00:08:31.887
[laughing]

184
00:08:31.888 --> 00:08:35.641
So it turns out my 12-year-old son
was not asleep in his own room.

185
00:08:35.642 --> 00:08:37.893
He had taken our car for a joyride.

186
00:08:37.894 --> 00:08:41.522
Now. he was arrested
for driving on the wrong side of the road.

187
00:08:41.523 --> 00:08:43.816
so I guess he was destined
to live in England.

188
00:08:43.817 --> 00:08:45.609
- [laughing]
- [speaks indistinctly in Spanish]

189
00:08:45.610 --> 00:08:49.071
Now. see. I wasn't 12. I was 15.
And the whole reason we got pulled over

190
00:08:49.072 --> 00:08:52.825
was 'cause Ronnie Fowch was throwing
gang signs at a cop car. [sighs]

191
00:08:52.826 --> 00:08:55.244
Look. sometimes the truth can ruin
a perfectly good story.

192
00:08:55.245 --> 00:08:57.831
- Yeah. you should work for the <i>Daily Mail</i>.
- [chuckles]

193
00:08:58.498 --> 00:09:01.877
Ted. if you can give your mom
one lovely moment.

194
00:09:02.544 --> 00:09:05.212
you know. a memory to take back home.
then you've won.

195
00:09:05.213 --> 00:09:08.549
- [team laughing. chattering]
- Hmm. Yeah. all right. Thanks. Boss.

196
00:09:08.550 --> 00:09:11.176
Right. I've got to go
and see a man about a horse.

197
00:09:11.177 --> 00:09:14.055
Oh. I didn't know girls said that
when they gotta pee. [chuckles]

198
00:09:14.806 --> 00:09:16.683
- No. Ted. I'm buying a horse.
- Oh.

199
00:09:17.434 --> 00:09:19.436
[team laughing. chattering]

200
00:09:20.687 --> 00:09:24.356
Hey. did Teddy ever tell you about
the time he ate a candy bar made of poop?

201
00:09:24.357 --> 00:09:27.151
- Ooh!
- Oh! Okay. okay! All right.

202
00:09:27.152 --> 00:09:29.778
I think that's enough story time
with Mama Lasso. all right. fellas?

203
00:09:29.779 --> 00:09:31.280
- [groans]
- Practice starts in twenty minutes.

204
00:09:31.281 --> 00:09:32.364
Up you go.

205
00:09:32.365 --> 00:09:34.408
- Nice to meet you. Mama Lasso.
- Nice to meet you.

206
00:09:34.409 --> 00:09:35.951
Hey. Mom. I'll be right back.

207
00:09:35.952 --> 00:09:38.287
I'm gonna go change.
and then I'll take you out to the pitch.

208
00:09:38.288 --> 00:09:40.123
Okay. honey. I'll be here.

209
00:09:41.207 --> 00:09:44.168
Mrs. Lasso. I just wanted to
introduce myself. I'm Trent Crimm.

210
00:09:44.169 --> 00:09:46.003
- Oh. hello. Trent.
- Hello.

211
00:09:46.004 --> 00:09:48.964
I was wondering if I could. uh.
just have a little chat with you about...

212
00:09:48.965 --> 00:09:50.591
Trent. your hair is fabulous.

213
00:09:50.592 --> 00:09:53.192
- It really is. It's just styling.
- [Trent] Thank you. Thank you.

214
00:09:54.554 --> 00:09:55.930
- [groans]
- Van Damme.

215
00:09:55.931 --> 00:09:57.491
- Hmm?
- You still gotta wear that mask?

216
00:09:57.891 --> 00:10:01.269
Yeah. I do. man. Or else I die.

217
00:10:04.231 --> 00:10:05.981
[speaks French]

218
00:10:05.982 --> 00:10:09.860
Between wearing that mask and death.
I choose death.

219
00:10:09.861 --> 00:10:12.529
- [teammates chuckle]
- It does make you look very stupid.

220
00:10:12.530 --> 00:10:15.282
- Oh. well. Thank you. Jan Maas.
- [Bumbercatch laughs]

221
00:10:15.283 --> 00:10:16.367
[sniffs]

222
00:10:16.368 --> 00:10:18.994
[teammates chattering]

223
00:10:18.995 --> 00:10:20.497
Oh. you wanna take a crack. Jamie?

224
00:10:22.332 --> 00:10:24.584
I think it's more important
to be safe than to look cool.

225
00:10:30.757 --> 00:10:32.634
Oi! Tartt.

226
00:10:33.343 --> 00:10:35.345
Boot room. Now!

227
00:10:39.766 --> 00:10:42.101
Somebody is in trouble.

228
00:10:42.102 --> 00:10:46.272
[clicks tongue] Mmm. no.
Shouting is Roy's love language.

229
