00:37:16.446 --> 00:37:17.656
I don't wanna be friends.

703
00:37:19.783 --> 00:37:22.619
- You don't?
- Uh-uh.

704
00:37:23.870 --> 00:37:27.249
I don't wanna be just friends.

705
00:37:37.342 --> 00:37:38.717
- Roy...
- [door opens]

706
00:37:38.718 --> 00:37:40.478
Well. guys.
I think we should probably get...

707
00:37:42.055 --> 00:37:45.976
- Uh. you good to go?
- Yeah.

708
00:37:47.018 --> 00:37:48.019
Yeah.

709
00:37:48.812 --> 00:37:51.064
Right. [grunts]

710
00:37:52.732 --> 00:37:53.733
[groans]

711
00:37:59.739 --> 00:38:00.656
[door closes]

712
00:38:00.657 --> 00:38:02.157
- [Jamie] I love you.
- [Georgie] I love you.

713
00:38:02.158 --> 00:38:04.201
- [Jamie] Good to see you.
- [Georgie] Good to see you too.

714
00:38:04.202 --> 00:38:05.953
[groans] Right.

715
00:38:05.954 --> 00:38:07.413
Hey. listen to me.

716
00:38:07.414 --> 00:38:10.207
I don't care
if you lose by ten goals tomorrow.

717
00:38:10.208 --> 00:38:12.836
I just want you to be happy. Okay. Son?

718
00:38:13.795 --> 00:38:17.089
Okay. Love you. Mommy. [kisses]

719
00:38:17.090 --> 00:38:18.299
I love you.

720
00:38:18.300 --> 00:38:20.634
[Jamie] Mmm. See you soon.

721
00:38:20.635 --> 00:38:22.177
See you soon. All right. come on.

722
00:38:22.178 --> 00:38:24.306
- Off you go. Go home.
- All right. Bye.

723
00:38:25.098 --> 00:38:26.516
It was great to meet you.

724
00:38:27.100 --> 00:38:28.225
Bye.

725
00:38:28.226 --> 00:38:30.978
- One for the road.
- [Keeley] Ooh. This way. babe.

726
00:38:30.979 --> 00:38:33.064
See you later. [kisses] Love... Love you.

727
00:38:39.195 --> 00:38:42.198
[Roy] We should go and have cocktails.
[chuckles]

728
00:38:51.207 --> 00:38:55.252
<i>...the latest in workout technology
like yoga mats!</i>

729
00:38:55.253 --> 00:38:56.212
[cell phone chimes]

730
00:38:56.213 --> 00:38:59.131
[Keeley] <i>Manchester has much to offer
when it comes to arts and culture.</i>

731
00:38:59.132 --> 00:39:02.302
{\an8}<i>including the Greater Manchester
Police Museum!</i>

732
00:39:03.470 --> 00:39:06.889
<i>The rainy city is also known
as well for science and technology.</i>

733
00:39:06.890 --> 00:39:10.476
{\an8}<i>for it was right here in 1917</i>

734
00:39:10.477 --> 00:39:14.272
{\an8}<i>that
Ernest Rutherford first split the atom.</i>

735
00:39:15.148 --> 00:39:19.235
{\an8}<i>And you'll split your sides laughing
at Manchester's many comedy clubs</i>

736
00:39:19.236 --> 00:39:22.446
{\an8}<i>and improvised murder mystery
dinner theaters. And. of course...</i>

737
00:39:22.447 --> 00:39:23.530
[sighs]

738
00:39:23.531 --> 00:39:27.243
[Keeley] <i>...your trip wouldn't be complete
without heading to Etihad Stadium.</i>

739
00:39:27.244 --> 00:39:31.664
- <i>home of the Manchester...</i> [voice fades]
- [fans singing] <i>Blue moon ♪</i>

740
00:39:31.665 --> 00:39:38.170
<i>You saw me standing alone ♪</i>

741
00:39:38.171 --> 00:39:44.969
{\an8} <i>Without a dream in my heart ♪</i>

742
00:39:44.970 --> 00:39:51.016
<i>Without a love of my own ♪</i>

743
00:39:51.017 --> 00:39:53.352
[cheering]

744
00:39:53.353 --> 00:39:58.774
<i>♪ I said. blue moon
You saw me standing alone ♪</i>

745
00:39:58.775 --> 00:40:03.279
<i>♪ Without a dream in my heart
Without a love of my own... ♪</i>

746
00:40:03.280 --> 00:40:06.198
Richmond should have a classic old song
for our fans to sing.

747
00:40:06.199 --> 00:40:08.075
- Hmm.
- Oh. we did.

748
00:40:08.076 --> 00:40:11.245
Uh. when Freddie Mercury
briefly owned the team in 1980.

749
00:40:11.246 --> 00:40:13.872
he tried to make "Fat Bottomed Girls"
the team anthem.

750
00:40:13.873 --> 00:40:15.332
- [chuckles]
- Didn't work out.

751
00:40:15.333 --> 00:40:17.293
Did a bunch of people get offended?

752
00:40:17.294 --> 00:40:19.795
Just the flat-bottomed girls really.

753
00:40:19.796 --> 00:40:21.046
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

754
00:40:21.047 --> 00:40:23.382
My father went to art school
with Freddie Mercury.

755
00:40:23.383 --> 00:40:24.758
- What?
- Mmm.

756
00:40:24.759 --> 00:40:29.305
I mean. everyone always talks
about his amazing four-octave vocal range.

757
00:40:29.306 --> 00:40:31.307
But my father always insisted

758
00:40:31.308 --> 00:40:34.894
that if you actually asked Freddie
what his greatest talent was.

759
00:40:34.895 --> 00:40:36.813
he would've said flipping straights.

760
00:40:38.815 --> 00:40:41.567
- [both] Come on. Richmond!
- You lads still have a way!

761
00:40:41.568 --> 00:40:42.652
[fans cheering]

762
00:40:44.654 --> 00:40:46.488
- Hey! Hey!
- [Baz exclaims]

763
00:40:46.489 --> 00:40:49.366
Hey. thanks for saving us a seat.
How long have you been waiting?

764
00:40:49.367 --> 00:40:51.076
Mae let me sleep here last night.

765
00:40:51.077 --> 00:40:53.914
- How many beers do you want?
- Three. Mae.

766
00:40:54.581 --> 00:40:58.001
How many beers do you want
if you can't order again before halftime?

767
00:40:58.668 --> 00:40:59.669
[all] Twelve.

768
00:41:00.378 --> 00:41:04.048
[Arlo] <i>Welcome. everyone. Today.
Manchester City hosts AFC Richmond.</i>

769
00:41:04.049 --> 00:41:09.178
<i>A first-ever win at the Etihad Stadium
for the Greyhounds. however unlikely.</i>

770
00:41:09.179 --> 00:41:12.056
<i>leaves the door open next week
for Ted Lasso's men</i>

771
00:41:12.057 --> 00:41:15.726
{\an8}<i>to complete the Cinderella story
their fans have been dreaming of.</i>

772
00:41:15.727 --> 00:41:17.311
Oh. there he is. Look at him.

773
00:41:17.312 --> 00:41:19.688
[Arlo] <i>The City faithful
are letting Jamie Tartt know</i>

774
00:41:19.689 --> 00:41:23.525
<i>how they feel about their former player
who left them for reality television.</i>

775
00:41:23.526 --> 00:41:26.737
- [Manchester City fans booing]
- Welcome home. dickhead! [laughs]

776
00:41:26.738 --> 00:41:29.449
[Arlo] <i>Perhaps not the homecoming
he might have dreamt of.</i>

777
00:41:30.867 --> 00:41:31.784
Oh. boy.

778
00:41:31.785 --> 00:41:35.496
Come on. Son. That's it. that's it.
Fucking bastards.

779
00:41:35.497 --> 00:41:38.040
[Arlo] <i>City can clinch the title
with a win today.</i>

780
00:41:38.041 --> 00:41:41.377
A loss makes things
very interesting next week.

781
00:41:41.378 --> 00:41:45.005
We find out in 90 minutes that starts now.

782
00:41:45.006 --> 00:41:45.924
[whistle blows]

783
00:41:48.051 --> 00:41:50.345
[Manchester City fans booing]

784
00:41:50.929 --> 00:41:52.763
[Arlo] <i>Ooh. clattered!</i>

785
00:41:52.764 --> 00:41:55.057
[Chris]
<i>Tartt can expect a lot of that today.</i>

786
00:41:55.058 --> 00:41:57.519
[booing continues]

787
00:42:03.191 --> 00:42:06.820
Here are some complimentary nuts.
And I'll be back to get your drinks. Okay?

788
00:42:07.529 --> 00:42:11.199
[Arlo] <i>Physical play from City
as Tartt pushes Richmond forward.</i>

789
00:42:12.200 --> 00:42:14.953
- <i>Tartt has options.</i>
- Colin's open.

790
00:42:16.997 --> 00:42:19.373
[Arlo] <i>Oh. a nifty move finds Bumbercatch.</i>

791
00:42:19.374 --> 00:42:20.624
<i>The Swiss crosses to the far post.</i>

792
00:42:20.625 --> 00:42:22.626
- <i>Hughes!</i>
- [fans cheering]

793
00:42:22.627 --> 00:42:24.420
- [Arlo] <i>The match has barely begun...</i>
- Yes.

794
00:42:24.421 --> 00:42:26.630
- <i>...and the Welshman fires the Greyhounds...</i>
- [both cheer]

795
00:42:26.631 --> 00:42:29.466
- <i>...into the lead with a commanding header.</i>
- [both cheer]

796
00:42:29.467 --> 00:42:30.885
There we go.

797
00:42:30.886 --> 00:42:34.388
[Chris] <i>That goal was all down to Tartt.
He's seeing two passes ahead.</i>

798
00:42:34.389 --> 00:42:37.516
[Arlo] <i>Brilliant play indeed
from the unsinkable Jamie Tartt.</i>

799
00:42:37.517 --> 00:42:42.313
<i>Colin Hughes with the exclamation point.
and Richmond leads 1-nil.</i>

800
00:42:42.314 --> 00:42:46.108
[patrons cheering]

801
00:42:46.109 --> 00:42:50.405
- [laughs. cheers]
- [squeals] Yes!

802
00:42:51.239 --> 00:42:52.615
Leslie. what you doing?

803
00:42:52.616 --> 00:42:55.326
I'll celebrate
when the final whistle has blown.

804
00:42:55.327 --> 00:42:57.120
I don't wanna move and jinx it.

805
00:42:58.413 --> 00:43:01.583
- Okay. [cheering]
- [Keeley cheering]

806
00:43:03.752 --> 00:43:05.961
[Arlo] <i>With the great Pep Guardiola
at the controls.</i>

807
00:43:05.962 --> 00:43:09.173
<i>rest assured.
City won't be quaking in their boots.</i>

808
00:43:09.174 --> 00:43:11.967
What's this sharp-dressed son of a gun
got cookin' now. huh?

809
00:43:11.968 --> 00:43:13.052
Go.

810
00:43:13.053 --> 00:43:15.554
[Chris] <i>You know Pep will make
the right adjustments. He always does.</i>

811
00:43:15.555 --> 00:43:16.640
Hold on tight.

812
00:43:17.349 --> 00:43:18.474
All right! Here we go!

813
00:43:18.475 --> 00:43:22.770
[Arlo] <i>Halftime approaches. and the
Premier League title remains undecided.</i>

814
00:43:22.771 --> 00:43:24.230
[Manchester City fans booing]

815
00:43:24.231 --> 00:43:27.400
[Arlo] <i>Jamie Tartt's hometown fans
are still letting him have it.</i>

816
00:43:28.443 --> 00:43:31.278
<i>City continuing to target
Richmond's number nine.</i>

817
00:43:31.279 --> 00:43:34.074
<i>Case in point.
as Tartt is knocked off the ball.</i>

818
00:43:38.119 --> 00:43:39.995
<i>And here comes City.</i>

819
00:43:39.996 --> 00:43:44.042
<i>De Villardi shoots!
Van Damme makes a terrific save.</i>

820
00:43:46.586 --> 00:43:50.173
<i>City making Tartt fight
for every inch out there.</i>

821
00:43:52.425 --> 00:43:55.010
Piss off back down South. pretty boy!

822
00:43:55.011 --> 00:43:58.223
[Arlo] <i>Tough crowd. Jamie Tartt.
Tough crowd.</i>

823
00:43:58.807 --> 00:44:00.307
<i>We're in the 65th minute.</i>

824
00:44:00.308 --> 00:44:03.602
And since Richmond's early goal.
it's been one-way traffic.

825
00:44:03.603 --> 00:44:08.441
<i>City asking plenty of questions.
but so far Richmond are not listening.</i>

826
00:44:10.986 --> 00:44:13.113
<i>Oh. a sliver of space for De Villardi.</i>

827
00:44:13.697 --> 00:44:15.531
<i>Is this the equalizer?</i>

828
00:44:15.532 --> 00:44:19.493
<i>No! A swashbuckling save
by the masked Canadian.</i>

829
00:44:19.494 --> 00:44:20.953
[Chris] <i>Van damn he's been good today!</i>

830
00:44:20.954 --> 00:44:22.329
- [all cheering]
- Come on!

831
00:44:22.330 --> 00:44:23.414
Yeah!

832
00:44:23.415 --> 00:44:25.874
[Arlo] <i>Nearing the 80-minute mark.</i>

833
00:44:25.875 --> 00:44:27.555
<i>Richmond are defending
their one-goal lead.</i>

834
00:44:29.421 --> 00:44:31.255
{\an8}<i>Ndour takes the corner.</i>

835
00:44:31.256 --> 00:44:34.508
{\an8}<i>Van Damme races off his line to punch.
but it finds Elokobi.</i>

836
00:44:34.509 --> 00:44:36.260
{\an8}<i>De Villardi has an open goal.</i>

837
00:44:36.261 --> 00:44:39.430
{\an8}- <i>Jamie Tartt soars to clear the danger!</i>
- Yes. Jamie!

838
00:44:39.431 --> 00:44:40.848
[all cheering]

839
00:44:40.849 --> 00:44:41.932
Yes. Jamie!

840
00:44:41.933 --> 00:44:43.851
- [Jamie groans]
- [Arlo] <i>Oh. no.</i>

841
00:44:43.852 --> 00:44:46.353
<i>It looks like Tartt
is in quite a bit of pain.</i>

842
00:44:46.354 --> 00:44:48.147
- [players clamoring]
- [Chris] <i>It's his ankle. Arlo.</i>

843
00:44:48.148 --> 00:44:51.066
- <i>He landed on it wrong.</i>
- Get up. you soft prick!

844
00:44:51.067 --> 00:44:53.611
[crowd laughing]

845
00:44:53.612 --> 00:44:54.695
Come on.

846
00:44:54.696 --> 00:44:56.031
Is he okay?

847
00:44:56.531 --> 00:44:57.532
[Thierry] Let's go.

848
00:45:00.327 --> 00:45:01.453
Roberts! Get warm.

849
00:45:01.953 --> 00:45:03.753
- I'm good. good. Go. bro. Go. go.
- You good?

850
00:45:04.205 --> 00:45:05.290
{\an8}[Jamie grunts]

851
00:45:07.334 --> 00:45:10.211
Now hold on. He's up.
he's up. he's up. Okay.

852
00:45:10.212 --> 00:45:12.087
[Arlo] <i>It appears he'll give it a go.</i>

853
00:45:12.088 --> 00:45:15.799
<i>Good news for Richmond. who
can ill afford to play without their star.</i>

854
00:45:15.800 --> 00:45:18.136
<i>Not with this much at stake.</i>

855
00:45:21.056 --> 00:45:22.974
[groans]

856
00:45:23.516 --> 00:45:24.600
- [all groan]
- [whistle blows]

857
00:45:24.601 --> 00:45:26.101
[Arlo] <i>We may have spoken too soon. Chris.</i>

858
00:45:26.102 --> 00:45:30.481
<i>Tartt tried to soldier on. but now he's in
some distress and may require attention.</i>

859
00:45:30.482 --> 00:45:31.566
Oh. my God.

860
00:45:37.155 --> 00:45:39.157
- [grunting]
- [medic 1] Up you go.

861
00:45:40.033 --> 00:45:41.233
[medic 2] Get you on the walk.

862
00:45:41.785 --> 00:45:43.452
Fudge.

863
00:45:43.453 --> 00:45:45.455
[fans applauding. whistling]

864
00:45:50.877 --> 00:45:52.127
- We're finished. We're done.
- Come on.

865
00:45:52.128 --> 00:45:53.838
- We're done.
- Come on. James.

866
00:45:56.800 --> 00:45:59.009
Roberts! You're going in.

867
00:45:59.010 --> 00:46:00.636
Whoa. hold on. hold on. Hey. hey.

868
00:46:00.637 --> 00:46:02.437
hey. don't hop out there
quite yet. Tan. okay?

869
00:46:02.931 --> 00:46:05.611
- Coach. we're a man down.
- I know. Coach. Just give me one second.

870
00:46:06.768 --> 00:46:08.811
Hey. Jamie. are you sure
you can't get back out there?

871
00:46:08.812 --> 00:46:11.438
- Uh. yeah.
- Yeah?

872
00:46:11.439 --> 00:46:12.731
- No.
- Hmm?

873
00:46:12.732 --> 00:46:15.609
- Hey. Coach! You wanna play with ten men?
- [Ted] Yeah.

874
00:46:15.610 --> 00:46:18.280
Heck yeah! [chuckles]
Right. eh? [clicks tongue]

875
00:46:18.989 --> 00:46:20.782
We're just gonna wait and see. okay?

876
00:46:21.700 --> 00:46:23.325
And we'll check in on you. all right?

877
00:46:23.326 --> 00:46:26.538
You two. do me a favor. Heal him.
Use all your tricks. please.

878
00:46:28.206 --> 00:46:30.708
Okay. Yeah.
We're gonna give him a couple minutes.

879
00:46:30.709 --> 00:46:33.586
- He's gonna be fine. Here we go. Come on!
- [Arlo] <i>Ted Lasso elects to wait.</i>

880
00:46:33.587 --> 00:46:37.131
<i>leaving ten Greyhounds
against City's mighty 11.</i>

881
00:46:37.132 --> 00:46:39.633
- [crowd roaring]
- [Arlo] <i>City looking for the equalizer.</i>

882
00:46:39.634 --> 00:46:42.887
<i>And Orellano shoots.
Van Damme is there! And there again!</i>

883
00:46:42.888 --> 00:46:44.096
[fans cheering]

884
00:46:44.097 --> 00:46:45.472
[Arlo] <i>And again!</i>

885
00:46:45.473 --> 00:46:48.893
<i>There's just no penetrating
the mask of Van Damme!</i>

886
00:46:48.894 --> 00:46:51.228
<i>With his team facing relentless pressure.</i>

887
00:46:51.229 --> 00:46:53.022
- <i>Ted Lasso is gambling with each...</i>
- [sniffs]

888
00:46:53.023 --> 00:46:55.274
- <i>...passing second he plays with a man down.</i>
- I'm gonna need a word. Nate.

889
00:46:55.275 --> 00:46:56.650
- In my office. yeah?
- Yeah.

890
00:46:56.651 --> 00:46:59.278
[Chris] <i>I love gambling.
Makes me feel alive.</i>

891
00:46:59.279 --> 00:47:01.719
[Arlo] <i>You should probably talk
to somebody about that. Chris.</i>

892
00:47:02.741 --> 00:47:05.243
Hello. mate. Come in. Take a seat.

893
00:47:06.036 --> 00:47:08.246
Here we go. [sighs] Mmm.

894
00:47:10.290 --> 00:47:12.833
[sighs] Am I getting promoted?

895
00:47:12.834 --> 00:47:14.753
[sighs] Nate. I gotta let you go.

896
00:47:15.462 --> 00:47:19.173
- W-Was it 'cause I was watching telly?
- No.

897
00:47:19.174 --> 00:47:20.507
I'm not pushing desserts hard enough?

898
00:47:20.508 --> 00:47:22.927
No. no. no.
It's... It's nothing you've done.

899
00:47:22.928 --> 00:47:27.807
You're my top man. You're on time.
you don't steal. you're sober.

900
00:47:28.308 --> 00:47:30.477
You're like my little unicorn.
You know what I mean?

901
00:47:31.311 --> 00:47:35.564
And it breaks my heart to say this.
but Jade said if I didn't fire you.

902
00:47:35.565 --> 00:47:37.067
she was gonna report me to the...

903
00:47:37.984 --> 00:47:40.069
Well. I can't say who.
because then you'd know what I've done.

904
00:47:40.070 --> 00:47:43.781
But... [clears throat] ...my
hands are tied. You gotta go.

905
00:47:43.782 --> 00:47:46.993
[breathes shakily] Yeah.

906
00:47:48.411 --> 00:47:50.789
[fans cheering]

907
00:47:55.210 --> 00:47:56.460
[Roy. Coach Beard] Yeah!

908
00:47:56.461 --> 00:47:58.212
[Arlo] <i>Chris.
Richmond aren't playing with a keeper.</i>

909
00:47:58.213 --> 00:48:00.297
<i>They've got a brick wall
in front of the goal.</i>

910
00:48:00.298 --> 00:48:03.217
[Chris] <i>No. Arlo. that's a person.
I can see his arms and legs.</i>

911
00:48:03.218 --> 00:48:04.760
<i>And his hideous mask.</i>

912
00:48:04.761 --> 00:48:08.347
[Arlo] <i>It seems like it's only
a matter of time before City equalize.</i>

913
00:48:08.348 --> 00:48:11.559
<i>That's all they need
to clinch the league title today.</i>

914
00:48:11.560 --> 00:48:13.562
Hey. Coach.
I don't want Jamie to play hurt.

915
00:48:14.062 --> 00:48:15.521
But we gotta make a decision here.

916
00:48:15.522 --> 00:48:16.939
Personally.
I'm fine with him playing hurt.

917
00:48:16.940 --> 00:48:18.148
I played hurt all the time.

918
00:48:18.149 --> 00:48:19.608
You can't walk up stairs.

919
00:48:19.609 --> 00:48:22.070
Okay. Let me go check. all right?

920
00:48:23.572 --> 00:48:25.574
- Thanks. y'all. Thank you.
- [breathing heavily]

921
00:48:28.326 --> 00:48:29.828
What you looking for up there. Jamie?

922
00:48:30.412 --> 00:48:33.581
Looking for my dad. I can't find him.
It's freaking me the fuck out.

923
00:48:33.582 --> 00:48:34.707
[Ted] Yeah. I get that.

924
00:48:34.708 --> 00:48:37.167
It's like when you don't know
where Freddy Krueger is.

925
00:48:37.168 --> 00:48:39.086
'Cause you know it's the second
he's gonna pop up

926
00:48:39.087 --> 00:48:40.754
and stick that knife-hand of his
in your face.

927
00:48:40.755 --> 00:48:42.673
Yeah. Freddy Krueger's fucking terrifying.

928
00:48:42.674 --> 00:48:44.425
Yeah. well. he had a rough childhood.

929
00:48:44.426 --> 00:48:46.093
And as we all know.
hurt people hurt people.

930
00:48:46.094 --> 00:48:48.138
Sometimes they just do it
with their knife-hands.

931
00:48:48.638 --> 00:48:50.158
When's the last time you saw your dad?

932
00:48:51.099 --> 00:48:55.186
- Wembley. [pants]
- Hmm. Y'all talk since then?

933
00:48:56.187 --> 00:48:58.397
- Nope. [sighs]
- Hmm.

934
00:48:58.398 --> 00:49:00.441
Okay. If you could talk to him now.
what would you say?

935
00:49:00.442 --> 00:49:02.234
I'd say. "Fuck you." [sighs]

936
00:49:02.235 --> 00:49:04.111
- Mmm. yeah. Makes sense.
- [sighs]

937
00:49:04.112 --> 00:49:05.947
- Anything else?
- Yeah.

938
00:49:06.615 --> 00:49:09.034
Yeah. I'd say. "Thank you."

939
00:49:13.622 --> 00:49:16.373
You know. Jamie. if hating your Pops
ain't motivating you like it used to.

940
00:49:16.374 --> 00:49:18.094
it might be time
to try something different.

941
00:49:20.045 --> 00:49:21.213
Just forgive him.

942
00:49:21.755 --> 00:49:23.380
Oh. fuck no. I ain't giving him that.

943
00:49:23.381 --> 00:49:25.592
Mm-mmm. no. You ain't giving him anything.

944
00:49:26.092 --> 00:49:29.638
When you choose to do that.
you're giving that to yourself.

945
00:49:30.305 --> 00:49:32.140
[crowd cheers]

946
00:49:37.270 --> 00:49:39.898
- Come on. [grunts]
- Okay. [grunting]

947
00:49:40.398 --> 00:49:41.918
- How do you feel?
- [exhaling heavily]

948
00:49:42.651 --> 00:49:46.029
- Yeah. Yeah. I feel good. Coach. Yeah.
- Yeah. See. the talk helped. right?

949
00:49:47.155 --> 00:49:49.436
Mostly the painkillers and the adrenaline.
I think. But...

950
00:49:49.824 --> 00:49:51.825
But yeah. the talk helped. yeah.

951
00:49:51.826 --> 00:49:54.662
Good. Now get your buns out there.
Let's go.

952
00:49:54.663 --> 00:49:56.081
[Jamie] Okay. okay.

953
00:49:56.665 --> 00:49:58.667
[Manchester City fans booing]

954
00:50:05.423 --> 00:50:06.424
Come on.

955
00:50:10.637 --> 00:50:12.973
Here we fucking go. Come on. Jamie!

956
00:50:14.349 --> 00:50:17.434
[Arlo] <i>Jamie Tartt
with a dramatic return to play.</i>

957
00:50:17.435 --> 00:50:20.312
<i>And he makes sure
he lets the City fans know all about it.</i>

958
00:50:20.313 --> 00:50:22.565
[booing]

959
00:50:22.566 --> 00:50:25.860
That's it. baby! You fucking show 'em!

960
00:50:27.487 --> 00:50:28.387
[whistle blows]

961
00:50:30.031 --> 00:50:31.073
Hey. come on. come on. come on.

962
00:50:31.074 --> 00:50:33.450
[all cheering. singing]
<i>Jamie Tartt. do. do. do. do. do. do ♪</i>

963
00:50:33.451 --> 00:50:35.287
<i>♪ Jamie Tartt
Do. do. do. do. do. do ♪</i>

964
00:50:36.705 --> 00:50:41.083
[Arlo] <i>Richmond have their backs
against the wall. It's De Villardi again.</i>

965
00:50:41.084 --> 00:50:43.210
<i>But Van Damme collects comfortably.</i>

966
00:50:43.211 --> 00:50:48.633
<i>And the Canadian. wasting no time.
finds McAdoo. And Richmond are off!</i>

967
00:50:49.885 --> 00:50:51.969
<i>Oh. that's astonishing control from Tartt!</i>

968
00:50:51.970 --> 00:50:53.429
Ooh! Ooh!

969
00:50:53.430 --> 00:50:56.182
- What's happening? Thank you.
- Oh!

970
00:50:57.434 --> 00:50:58.518
[Arlo] <i>Tartt cuts inside.</i>

971
00:50:59.561 --> 00:51:00.562
<i>And again.</i>

972
00:51:01.980 --> 00:51:03.732
<i>Oh. he's untouchable!</i>

973
00:51:07.611 --> 00:51:10.363
- [foot impacts ball]
- [whooshing]

974
00:51:11.197 --> 00:51:13.199
- [ball hits net]
- [fans cheering]

975
00:51:14.284 --> 00:51:17.244
- [cheers] Go. Jamie!
- Yes! Yeah! [cheers]

976
00:51:17.245 --> 00:51:20.539
[all shouting. cheering]

977
00:51:20.540 --> 00:51:24.168
[Arlo] <i>And Jamie Tartt
all but clinches the win for Richmond</i>

978
00:51:24.169 --> 00:51:26.962
- <i>with a spectacular solo goal!</i>
- My goodness! Did you see that?

979
00:51:26.963 --> 00:51:29.633
- [cheering. screaming]
- Yes. Jamie!

980
00:51:31.092 --> 00:51:33.385
[Arlo] <i>And a class move
from the native Mancunian.</i>

981
00:51:33.386 --> 00:51:36.514
<i>not to celebrate against his former club.</i>

982
00:51:39.059 --> 00:51:40.060
[whistle blows]

983
00:51:40.644 --> 00:51:43.355
[Arlo]
<i>And Richmond with a late substitution.</i>

984
00:51:48.652 --> 00:51:49.653
Attaboy. Jamie!

985
00:51:53.198 --> 00:51:54.282
[player] Well done.

986
00:51:57.244 --> 00:52:00.454
- Jamie Tartt. you fucking king!
- [fans cheering]

987
00:52:00.455 --> 00:52:02.289
{\an8}- [fans applauding]
- [Arlo] <i>Tartt makes way.</i>

988
00:52:02.290 --> 00:52:05.543
{\an8}<i>And listen to this response
from the City supporters.</i>

989
00:52:05.544 --> 00:52:09.046
{\an8}<i>an ovation for a visiting player
who was also one of their own.</i>

990
00:52:09.047 --> 00:52:11.840
- <i>You don't hear this every day.</i>
- Come on.

991
00:52:11.841 --> 00:52:14.593
[Arlo] <i>Just think of what it means
for Tartt to hear this.</i>

992
00:52:14.594 --> 00:52:17.221
- <i>And what it means for his family.</i>
- [sighs] Yes. Oh. my God.

993
00:52:17.222 --> 00:52:19.182
- [mumbles]
- Oh. my God.

994
00:52:21.518 --> 00:52:24.603
- [laughing]
- [screaming]

995
00:52:24.604 --> 00:52:27.731
- Fucking beautiful. [gasps]
- That was amazing.

996
00:52:27.732 --> 00:52:29.693
[sighing]

997
00:52:36.199 --> 00:52:37.200
Jamie.

998
00:52:37.826 --> 00:52:39.160
[Roy whispers]

999
00:52:46.668 --> 00:52:47.710
He's a tough kid.

1000
00:52:47.711 --> 00:52:49.379
His dad would have been proud.

1001
00:52:53.091 --> 00:52:55.010
[applauding]

1002
00:52:55.635 --> 00:52:57.094
[Arlo] <i>Credit where it's due.</i>

1003
00:52:57.095 --> 00:53:00.431
<i>Lasso rolled the dice on Tartt's fitness
and the team's talisman</i>

1004
00:53:00.432 --> 00:53:01.975
<i>rose to the occasion.</i>

1005
00:53:03.727 --> 00:53:06.729
<i>With time running out.
City try and cross into the box.</i>

1006
00:53:06.730 --> 00:53:08.188
<i>But again. Van Damme is there.</i>

1007
00:53:08.189 --> 00:53:10.649
- [whistle blowing]
- [cheers]

1008
00:53:10.650 --> 00:53:13.235
[screaming. cheering]

1009
00:53:13.236 --> 00:53:16.447
[Arlo] <i>And after
that sterling performance from Richmond.</i>

1010
00:53:16.448 --> 00:53:20.034
<i>the Premier League title will come down
to the final week of the season.</i>

1011
00:53:20.035 --> 00:53:22.661
<i>Chris. they could win
the whole effing thing!</i>

1012
00:53:22.662 --> 00:53:25.247
[Chris] <i>Sorry for
the almost brutal language there. folks.</i>

1013
00:53:25.248 --> 00:53:27.791
- It's that time. Holy crap.
- [laughing]

1014
00:53:27.792 --> 00:53:30.711
- Good game. Congratulations.
- Thanks. Coach. I appreciate it.

1015
00:53:30.712 --> 00:53:33.047
Hey. I gotta be honest with you.
You're a tough guy to beat. man.

1016
00:53:33.048 --> 00:53:36.133
[chuckles]
Nah. don't worry about wins or losses.

1017
00:53:36.134 --> 00:53:39.595
Just help these guys be the best version
of themselves on and off the pitch.

1018
00:53:39.596 --> 00:53:41.263
This. at the end.
is the most important thing.

1019
00:53:41.264 --> 00:53:42.890
I couldn't agree more. Coach.

1020
00:53:42.891 --> 00:53:44.392
All right. then. Take care.

1021
00:53:46.436 --> 00:53:47.437
[gasps]

1022
00:53:48.063 --> 00:53:49.104
[screams]

1023
00:53:49.105 --> 00:53:51.732
Oh. my God. Oh. my God. Oh. my God.
Oh. my God. Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1024
00:53:51.733 --> 00:53:54.277
- Boss. Hey. it's good to see you.
- Good to see you too.

1025
00:53:54.778 --> 00:53:59.074
[no audio]

1026
00:54:00.909 --> 00:54:02.494
[players cheering]

1027
00:54:21.721 --> 00:54:23.723
[chattering]

1028
00:54:27.894 --> 00:54:30.437
- All right. lads. Listen up.
- [player] All right. Yo. what's up?

1029
00:54:30.438 --> 00:54:32.648
We've got one more game. so that means

1030
00:54:32.649 --> 00:54:35.150
a glass of water with every single
alcoholic beverage tonight. all right?

1031
00:54:35.151 --> 00:54:36.735
[players cheering]

1032
00:54:36.736 --> 00:54:38.988
- We rolling?
- No. no. I've gotta get this sorted out.

1033
00:54:38.989 --> 00:54:40.447
But you have fun with your water. yeah?

1034
00:54:40.448 --> 00:54:42.534
[chuckles]

1035
00:54:44.411 --> 00:54:46.078
- [Cockburn] There's my lad. Do you proud.
- Nice.

1036
00:54:46.079 --> 00:54:48.163
- Yeah. you bet. bruv. All right. love.
- Hey. take care. bruv.

1037
00:54:48.164 --> 00:54:49.415
- Love.
- That's what I like. man.

1038
00:54:49.416 --> 00:54:51.041
- Be good. Be good.
- [Colin] Rest up. man.

1039
00:54:51.042 --> 00:54:52.877
Hey. listen. man.
I wanna say I'm proud of you.

1040
00:54:52.878 --> 00:54:55.462
- You played so well today. man.
- Ah. appreciate it. man.

1041
00:54:55.463 --> 00:54:57.507
- You scored a goal. Come on. Hey.
- Thanks. Jamie.

1042
00:54:58.008 --> 00:54:59.592
[speaks Spanish] Well done tonight.

1043
00:54:59.593 --> 00:55:01.344
Thank you. man. Big love. amigo.

1044
00:55:05.557 --> 00:55:06.557
[sighs]

1045
00:55:06.558 --> 00:55:11.313
[whistling] All right. buddy.

1046
00:55:11.813 --> 00:55:13.564
I will see you at karaoke.

1047
00:55:13.565 --> 00:55:16.734
I will of course sign us up
for "Islands in the Stream."

1048
00:55:16.735 --> 00:55:18.402
But I'm calling dibs on Dolly.
[snaps fingers]

1049
00:55:18.403 --> 00:55:19.905
No can do. Coach. [sighs]

1050
00:55:21.323 --> 00:55:23.657
Mom's cooking dinner tonight.
Last night in town.

1051
00:55:23.658 --> 00:55:25.951
All right. Well. give Dottie my love.

1052
00:55:25.952 --> 00:55:30.707
Will do. Actually. hold on a sec. Coach.
Come here. Check this out. [chuckles]

1053
00:55:35.795 --> 00:55:38.797
- Uh...
- No. no. I know you've already seen it.

1054
00:55:38.798 --> 00:55:41.559
I just don't know if you've watched
the whole thing. Look. Look. look.

1055
00:55:42.969 --> 00:55:43.970
All right.

1056
00:55:44.888 --> 00:55:46.555
So look. After we came in.

1057
00:55:46.556 --> 00:55:50.309
Nate had to hide under my desk here
for. like. three whole hours

1058
00:55:50.310 --> 00:55:55.314
while we were all whooping and hollering
and celebrating all around him. [chuckles]

1059
00:55:55.315 --> 00:55:58.485
Then. once we all split.
he thought he was in the clear.

1060
00:55:59.110 --> 00:56:01.153
And boom! Cleaning crew shows up.

1061
00:56:01.154 --> 00:56:05.992
Oh. man. That's another two hours
under that desk. Yep.

1062
00:56:08.078 --> 00:56:10.914
Well. then after they leave.
he crawls out.

1063
00:56:11.539 --> 00:56:14.708
His legs just gotta be jelly.
He can barely stand up.

1064
00:56:14.709 --> 00:56:19.838
Look at this. He goes to check the doors.
but they're all locked! [chuckles]

1065
00:56:19.839 --> 00:56:21.674
Oh. man. that son of a gun

1066
00:56:21.675 --> 00:56:24.594
had to climb out the window here
just to get out of the building.

1067
00:56:25.303 --> 00:56:28.223
[chuckles. sighs]

1068
00:56:28.723 --> 00:56:30.182
You know. I don't know about you. Coach.

1069
00:56:30.183 --> 00:56:35.646
But I hope that either all of us
or none of us are judged

1070
00:56:35.647 --> 00:56:37.941
by the actions of our weakest moments.

1071
00:56:39.317 --> 00:56:41.986
but rather by the strength we show

1072
00:56:41.987 --> 00:56:46.616
when and if we're ever given
a second chance.

1073
00:56:50.203 --> 00:56:54.164
All right. have fun tonight. Coach.
[grunts]

1074
00:56:54.165 --> 00:56:58.253
<i>And we rely on each other. ah ha ♪</i>

1075
00:56:59.087 --> 00:57:02.798
[whistling]

1076
00:57:02.799 --> 00:57:05.051
Fuck.

1077
00:57:16.563 --> 00:57:17.643
[message sent sound effect]

1078
00:57:21.568 --> 00:57:22.736
[knocks]

1079
00:57:23.695 --> 00:57:26.488
- Hi.
- Hey. What are you guys doing?

1080
00:57:26.489 --> 00:57:28.449
We thought we'd come and keep you company.

1081
00:57:28.450 --> 00:57:31.035
- Fucking celebrate.
- Yeah!

1082
00:57:31.036 --> 00:57:33.622
- [Jamie chuckles]
- 'Cause that was fucking amazing. Jamie.

1083
00:57:34.289 --> 00:57:35.623
Yeah. I was fucking amazing. You're right.

1084
00:57:35.624 --> 00:57:37.625
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles] Yes.

1085
00:57:37.626 --> 00:57:39.377
- Ey!
- [Keeley] Whoo!

1086
00:57:40.754 --> 00:57:43.172
- You start us off.
- Mmm. Don't mind if I do.

1087
00:57:43.173 --> 00:57:46.383
Right.
What the fuck happened. man? [chuckles]

1088
00:57:46.384 --> 00:57:47.968
[Keeley chuckles]

1089
00:57:47.969 --> 00:57:52.848
- Did I look sexy? [chuckles]
- [laughing]

1090
00:57:52.849 --> 00:57:54.683
Shame you weren't injured
in your fucking head. innit?

1091
00:57:54.684 --> 00:57:56.394
- [chuckling]
- [laughs]

1092
00:57:59.522 --> 00:58:00.523
I'm back.

1093
00:58:02.400 --> 00:58:03.400
Hey. babe. You all right?

1094
00:58:03.401 --> 00:58:05.569
Someone never came for their pickup order.

1095
00:58:05.570 --> 00:58:08.156
Oh. thank you. Great.

1096
00:58:10.492 --> 00:58:15.413
So. um. I don't know if you heard.
but Derek fired me today.

1097
00:58:16.623 --> 00:58:18.457
That bastard!

1098
00:58:18.458 --> 00:58:21.711
- Yeah. I was devastated.
- [sighs]

1099
00:58:23.797 --> 00:58:26.966
But it made me realize that even though
there's only one match left.

1100
00:58:26.967 --> 00:58:29.636
I have to go back to Richmond.
To make things right.

1101
00:58:31.972 --> 00:58:33.556
Currently writing Ted an apology letter.

1102
00:58:33.557 --> 00:58:37.226
It's 60 pages. but I'm just looking
for a few trims. so...

1103
00:58:37.227 --> 00:58:39.187
- [doorbell rings]
- Ooh. [grunts] Two secs.

1104
00:58:40.438 --> 00:58:42.691
[sighs. mumbling] Sixty pages.

1105
00:58:45.360 --> 00:58:46.260
Oh. my God.

1106
00:58:59.207 --> 00:59:00.667
You here to kill me?

1107
00:59:02.335 --> 00:59:04.170
Ted and I met playing college football.

1108
00:59:05.547 --> 00:59:08.215
He was the backup punter.
I was the backup kicker.

1109
00:59:08.216 --> 00:59:09.551
We never got in a game.

1110
00:59:10.176 --> 00:59:14.014
but we spent a lot of time together.
jogging and doing box jumps.

1111
00:59:15.390 --> 00:59:16.932
After school. we went our separate ways.

1112
00:59:16.933 --> 00:59:19.477
And he was dating Michelle.
got into coaching.

1113
00:59:20.353 --> 00:59:21.438
And I got into prison.

1114
00:59:22.981 --> 00:59:24.149
When I got paroled...

1115
00:59:26.151 --> 00:59:29.529
I had no money. family didn't want me.
I had nowhere to go.

1116
00:59:30.447 --> 00:59:31.573
So I looked up Ted.

1117
00:59:33.742 --> 00:59:36.077
He took me in. fed me.

1118
00:59:37.245 --> 00:59:38.622
Let me crash on his couch.

1119
00:59:40.123 --> 00:59:43.376
And in return. I stole his car.

1120
00:59:45.086 --> 00:59:46.546
Now. I didn't get far.

1121
00:59:48.131 --> 00:59:51.675
And I would've gone straight back
to prison if Ted didn't come down there

1122
00:59:51.676 --> 00:59:54.679
and convince those cops
that he gave me the car.

1123
00:59:55.722 --> 00:59:56.722
Just like in <i>Les Mis</i>.

1124
00:59:56.723 --> 00:59:58.975
Our story is very similar to <i>Les Mis</i>. yes.

1125
00:59:59.559 --> 01:00:01.227
- You went to prison?
- Yes.

1126
01:00:01.228 --> 01:00:03.021
For stealing a loaf of meth.

1127
01:00:05.273 --> 01:00:06.733
And then I stole from my friend.

1128
01:00:09.110 --> 01:00:12.030
Who forgave me. [sighs]

1129
01:00:12.530 --> 01:00:15.867
And gave me a job. And a life.

1130
01:00:19.246 --> 01:00:22.207
So to honor that. I forgive you.

1131
01:00:24.167 --> 01:00:28.380
I offer you a job.
And the life part's up to you.

1132
01:00:35.595 --> 01:00:36.721
Thank you.

1133
01:00:39.349 --> 01:00:40.392
[sighs]

1134
01:00:42.769 --> 01:00:46.648
You sure you don't wanna headbutt me?
I think it might make us feel better.

1135
01:00:55.073 --> 01:00:57.158
[inhales deeply]

1136
01:01:01.955 --> 01:01:04.082
Monday. 10:00 a.m.

1137
01:01:09.713 --> 01:01:12.257
[breathes deeply]

1138
01:01:30.942 --> 01:01:33.777
- Hello?
- [Dottie] Ooh. welcome home. honey.

1139
01:01:33.778 --> 01:01:37.656
- Come take a seat. you must be starving.
- Yeah. okay.

1140
01:01:37.657 --> 01:01:40.826
Hey. congratulations on your big win.

1141
01:01:40.827 --> 01:01:44.413
I didn't know if you'd be in the mood
for meat loaf or lasagna. so I made both.

1142
01:01:44.414 --> 01:01:45.498
- [chuckles]
- [Ted] Hmm.

1143
01:01:49.336 --> 01:01:53.172
- Mom. what's wrong? Why are you here?
- What do you mean?

1144
01:01:53.173 --> 01:01:55.842
I mean. if you got something
you need to say to me.

1145
01:01:56.509 --> 01:01:58.260
I'd appreciate it
if you just went ahead and said it.

1146
01:01:58.261 --> 01:02:02.556
Oh. stop. I just want to spend
my last night in London with my son

1147
01:02:02.557 --> 01:02:04.475
and make sure everything's all right.

1148
01:02:04.476 --> 01:02:07.062
Mm-hmm. Yeah. okay.

1149
01:02:07.812 --> 01:02:10.105
Well. thank you for cooking dinner.
Both of 'em.

1150
01:02:10.106 --> 01:02:11.650
Oh. you're welcome.

1151
01:02:13.652 --> 01:02:17.029
- And fuck you for not wanting to talk.
- Excuse me?

1152
01:02:17.030 --> 01:02:20.074
Thank you for flying all the way here
to come see me.

1153
01:02:20.075 --> 01:02:21.955
and fuck you for not telling me
you were coming.

1154
01:02:23.161 --> 01:02:27.665
Thank you for all the small. silly. little
things you did for me as a kid. you know?

1155
01:02:27.666 --> 01:02:29.792
Like hiding notes in my lunch box

1156
01:02:29.793 --> 01:02:34.422
or. uh. putting googly eyes on the fruit
at the supermarket just to make me laugh.

1157
01:02:34.923 --> 01:02:38.050
And fuck you for not working on yourself

1158
01:02:38.051 --> 01:02:40.428
or seeking help after we lost dad.

1159
01:02:40.929 --> 01:02:42.763
And for not talking to me about it either.

1160
01:02:42.764 --> 01:02:44.473
Just glossing over the whole thing

1161
01:02:44.474 --> 01:02:47.310
and... and acting
like everything was all right.

1162
01:02:50.897 --> 01:02:53.400
- I'm sorry.
- Mm-hmm.

1163
01:02:55.235 --> 01:02:59.280
Um... [stammers]
...I didn't know what to do. Ted.

1164
01:02:59.281 --> 01:03:03.409
So. I pretended I was okay.

1165
01:03:03.410 --> 01:03:05.912
Okay. Well. thank you for the apology.

1166
01:03:06.413 --> 01:03:08.665
And fuck you for making me think
I had to pretend too.

1167
01:03:09.749 --> 01:03:13.336
All right. I... I appreciate you. uh.
sharing all this with me.

1168
01:03:15.088 --> 01:03:17.047
I just wish you hadn't carried it around
for so long.

1169
01:03:17.048 --> 01:03:18.967
[scoffs] Yeah. okay.

1170
01:03:19.551 --> 01:03:23.137
And. um. you're right. Ted.
I do have something to say to you.

1171
01:03:23.138 --> 01:03:24.723
[grunts] Hmm?

1172
01:03:26.099 --> 01:03:27.434
Your son misses you.

1173
01:03:32.480 --> 01:03:33.857
Yeah. I know.

1174
01:03:36.318 --> 01:03:37.819
I miss him too.

1175
01:03:44.576 --> 01:03:49.204
[sighs] It's just like I... [crying]

1176
01:03:49.205 --> 01:03:53.626
It's like I'm scared sometimes to. like...

1177
01:03:53.627 --> 01:03:57.047
[breathes shakily]
...to get close to that little boy.

1178
01:03:57.797 --> 01:03:59.507
Oh. honey. why?

1179
01:04:03.553 --> 01:04:05.263
'Cause I know he's gonna leave.

1180
01:04:11.102 --> 01:04:12.187
Oh. well...

1181
01:04:14.773 --> 01:04:18.067
- God. No. no. no. no. You know...
- [sniffs. sighs]

1182
01:04:18.068 --> 01:04:20.486
Oh. all right.
That is the thing about being a parent.

1183
01:04:20.487 --> 01:04:21.612
[sighs]

1184
01:04:21.613 --> 01:04:23.614
Sometimes you lose and...

1185
01:04:23.615 --> 01:04:27.786
[stammers] ...sometimes you win.
but most of the time you just tie.

1186
01:04:31.581 --> 01:04:34.542
All we can do is keep playing.

1187
01:04:36.378 --> 01:04:40.798
Right. [sighs. chuckles]

1188
01:04:40.799 --> 01:04:44.636
[sniffles] Hmm. Thank you.

1189
01:04:47.389 --> 01:04:51.184
- Fuck you. [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

1190
01:04:52.852 --> 01:04:54.437
Oh. my goodness.

1191
01:04:54.938 --> 01:04:57.357
I'm sorry about that. I...

1192
01:04:58.149 --> 01:05:00.401
[sighs] You know what?
Let me make it up to you. okay?

1193
01:05:00.402 --> 01:05:04.280
Why don't you take a seat? And I'll. uh...
And I'll serve you dinner for once. okay?

1194
01:05:04.281 --> 01:05:08.659
- [chuckles] What? Oh. Ooh. Okay.
- Come on now. pop a squat. Go on.

1195
01:05:08.660 --> 01:05:10.829
- Yeah. yeah. [sighs]
- [chuckles]

1196
01:05:11.538 --> 01:05:16.458
Hey. You know. uh. this therapist
must be doing you some good.

1197
01:05:16.459 --> 01:05:18.460
- Oh. boy.
- [chuckles]

1198
01:05:18.461 --> 01:05:20.379
I'm gonna leave her out of this.

1199
01:05:20.380 --> 01:05:24.425
Oh. wait till she hears about this. Okay.
You know what? Let's start with the wine.

1200
01:05:24.426 --> 01:05:26.636
- Let's do. please.
- [doorbell rings]

1201
01:05:30.181 --> 01:05:32.183
- Bex.
- Hi.

1202
01:05:32.684 --> 01:05:36.605
Sorry to just show up like this.
Um. I need some advice.

1203
01:05:37.981 --> 01:05:40.274
- Okay.
- Can we come in?

1204
01:05:40.275 --> 01:05:41.359
We?

1205
01:05:47.532 --> 01:05:48.533
Of course.

1206
01:07:00.689 --> 01:07:01.855
Morning. Will.

1207
01:07:01.856 --> 01:07:03.233
[Will] Hey. Good morning. Ted.

1208
01:07:12.075 --> 01:07:14.244
- Hey. Boss.
- Oh. Hello. Ted.

1209
01:07:15.078 --> 01:07:16.580
Do you know this John Wooden?

1210
01:07:17.080 --> 01:07:18.789
No. ma'am.
Never had the chance to meet him.

1211
01:07:18.790 --> 01:07:20.374
Oh. pity. I like this.

1212
01:07:20.375 --> 01:07:23.168
Ah. I mean. if you don't like that.
you don't like ice cream.

1213
01:07:23.169 --> 01:07:25.797
- [both chuckle]
- What's up?

1214
01:07:26.923 --> 01:07:29.925
- Do you know what time it is?
- Uh. 9:30.

1215
01:07:29.926 --> 01:07:33.596
Or half nine as you folks say over here
for some goofy-ass reason.

1216
01:07:33.597 --> 01:07:36.391
- Mm-hmm. That's just to annoy Americans.
- [chuckles] Ah. Yeah.

1217
01:07:38.643 --> 01:07:44.983
No. this is that time of year when I come
down here and reveal something to you.

1218
01:07:45.483 --> 01:07:48.569
Oh. snap. That's right. Okay.

1219
01:07:48.570 --> 01:07:50.654
- [stammers] Well. here we go.
- [sighs]

1220
01:07:50.655 --> 01:07:53.657
[chuckles] Uh. you know what?
Maybe I should guess this year.

1221
01:07:53.658 --> 01:07:55.367
No. no. no. that's silly. Yeah.

1222
01:07:55.368 --> 01:07:58.121
No. you just go ahead and tell me.
Go on. let 'er rip.

1223
01:08:00.206 --> 01:08:02.333
- I've got nothing.
- Hmm.

1224
01:08:02.334 --> 01:08:04.835
Oh. I really tried as well.
I mean. even on the walk over here.

1225
01:08:04.836 --> 01:08:07.922
I was thinking something would pop
into my head. but nope.

1226
01:08:07.923 --> 01:08:10.467
- Absolutely nothing. Sorry. Ted.
- Hmm.

1227
01:08:11.468 --> 01:08:14.094
No truth bomb this year.

1228
01:08:14.095 --> 01:08:19.267
Hmm. Well. that's okay.
[chuckles] I got one.
